###LOOPING###
if, else: testing a condition

for: execute a loop a fixed number of times

while: execute a loop while a condition is true

repeat: execute an infinite loop

break: break the execution of a loop

next: skip an interation of a loop

return: exit a function


###LOOP FUNCTIONS#######
lapply: Loop over a list and evaluate a function on each element. lapply returns a
list regardless of class of data table x.

lapply(x, mean or any other fn) #where x is a list. 



sapply: Same as lapply but try to simplify the result.
sapply(x, mean or any other fn) #where x is a list

apply: Apply a function over the margins of an array. It is mostly applied on arrays
and/or matrices


tapply: Apply a function over subsets of a vector


mapply: Multivariate version of lapply
